{
  "text": "There are very few data available in the literature on the outcome following radiofrequency ablation for hepatic metastasized gastric cancer [CITATION_1] . Within our study group, there were 5 patients who underwent that procedure and they showed an overall 5-year survival rate of 53%. Due to the less invasive approach and the repeatability of the procedure, radiofrequency ablation may become an alternative to hepatic resection, especially in cases of borderline resectability, as the procedure is successfully practised for other indications; however, studies of clinical outcomes in larger study groups are needed in the future.",
